HEADWORD: Bœotian
<hw>B⟦oe⟧*o"tian</hw> <pr>(b⟦esl⟧*⟦omac⟧"sh⟦ait⟧n)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>Boeotia</ets>, Gr. <grk>boiwti`a</grk>, noted for its
moist, thick atmosphere, and the dullness and stupidity of its
inhabitants.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to B⟦oe⟧otia.</def> --
<def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>A native of B⟦oe⟧otia; also, one who is dull
and ignorant.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <def>Stupid; dull; obtuse.</def>
-- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>One who is dull and
ignorant.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Boer</ent>⟦br⟧
